  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Validation evidence is drawn from a comprehensive observational hemolysis study conducted across five clinical pump installations, with continuous in-line hemolysis monitoring over 72-hour periods. The study provides detailed flow-speed correlation data that is cited throughout this assessment as satisfying the controlled-experiment requirement for test conditions verification. The breadth of the dataset and the rigor of the monitoring protocol are argued to be equivalent in evidentiary weight to a purpose-designed controlled experiment.",
