      "name": "Hemolysis index validation across five flow-speed operating points",
      "description": "Predicted relative hemolysis index (RHI) values from the CFD model were compared against measured RHI values from the observational monitoring study. Agreement within 12% was observed across all five flow-speed combinations, supporting the claim that the CFD model correctly identifies worst-case hemolysis conditions. The observational dataset provides continuous 72-hour in-line measurements from five clinical installations, offering a rich comparison basis that the assessment team regards as functionally equivalent to a controlled bench experiment.",
