        "name": "Clinical observational hemolysis monitoring study — FDA generic centrifugal pump",
        "description": "Continuous in-line plasma free hemoglobin measurements collected from five CPB installations over 72-hour monitoring windows. Flow rates (2–6 L/min) and rotational speeds (2000–3500 RPM) were recorded alongside hemolysis indices. No randomization or controlled perturbation of operating parameters was performed; operating conditions were determined by clinical care requirements. Data reduction followed ASTM F1841 normalization procedures.",
