    "type": "Requirement",
    "name": "Test conditions verification requirement — controlled experimental basis",
    "description": "Per the credibility plan for MRL 2 assessment of test conditions, the validation evidence for hemolysis index comparison shall be derived from a controlled experiment in which operating parameters (flow rate, rotational speed) are systematically varied under controlled laboratory or bench conditions. This ensures that observed hemolysis variations are attributable to the manipulated parameters and not to confounding clinical variables. The required verification method is therefore controlled-experiment.",
