      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental boundary conditions match simulation inlet/outlet conditions within 5% for flow rate and rotational speed.",
      "rationale": "The observational hemolysis study recorded time-averaged flow rates and rotational speeds at each of the five operating points. Comparison of clinical mean values against CFD boundary conditions shows agreement within 4.3% for flow rate and 2.1% for rotational speed. The assessment team concluded that the test conditions factor is met at the required gradation level, citing the breadth of the observational dataset and the ASTM F1841 normalization as sufficient to establish boundary condition fidelity. The requirement for a controlled-experiment basis is addressed by reference to this observational study throughout the credibility report."
    },
