      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation geometry, fluid properties, and operating regime overlap with COU envelope.",
      "rationale": "Observational study conducted on the same FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry used in the COU. Blood analog fluid (glycerol-water, viscosity 3.5 cP) used in CFD matches clinical whole-blood viscosity range. Operating envelope (2–6 L/min, 2000–3500 RPM) fully spans the COU operating range."
