    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required gradation levels for MRL 2. Six factors are appropriately scoped out at MRL 2. The CFD model is accepted as credible for identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device. Validation evidence from the observational hemolysis monitoring study demonstrates RHI prediction error below 15% across all five operating points, and the worst-case condition is correctly identified. The assessment team is satisfied that the totality of evidence supports the Accepted decision for this COU.",
